  "body": "# Bug Report\r\n\r\n## Problem\r\n\r\nWhen signing a message or typed data from a dApp using Keycard, the sign method is called without a path, which would use the current path on card instead of the active account. When using the default account this does not give problems, but when addings accounts to the multiaccount it means the signature generated will be wrong one.\r\n\r\n## Steps to reproduce\r\n\r\nUsing a Keycard multiaccount, create a second account. Open the browser and select that second account. Try to login to cryptokitties with that account and login will fail (because the signature will be generated by the wrong account)\r\n\r\n## Additional Information\r\nTest on release 1.10.1, develop branch from 17.02.2021 and PR11540. PR11540 tested on iOS as well.",
